{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place chocolate into mixing bowl and grate <b>8 sec\/speed 8<b>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula. Add coconut milk, sugar, egg yolks and salt (optional), then cook <b>8 min\/90°C\/speed 2<b> and blend <b>5 sec\/speed 4<b> <strong>-7, increasing speed gradually from speed 4 to speed 7<\/strong>.","Add cinnamon, ground chilli and vanilla. Blend <b>4 sec\/speed 5<b>. Pour mixture into a shallow freezable container and place into freezer (approx. 8 hours) until frozen. Clean and dry mixing bowl.","Cut the ice cream into pieces (3-4 cm) and place half of the ice cream pieces into mixing bowl and blend <b>20 sec\/speed 6<b>, then mix <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b>, with aid of spatula. Transfer into a freezable container and set aside.","Place remaining ice cream pieces into mixing bowl and blend <b>20 sec\/speed 6<b>, then mix <b>10 sec\/speed 4<b> with aid of spatula. Transfer into freezable container with ice cream.","Cover with plastic wrap and return to freezer for 4 hours or until set. Garnish with fresh chilli before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["200 g dairy free dark chocolate","500 gram unsweetened coconut milk","150 g sugar","4 egg yolks","1 pinch salt (optional)","1 tablespoon ground cinnamon","¼ teaspoon ground chilli","1 tbsp natural vanilla extract","2 fresh red chillies, deseeded if preferred, for garnishing"]}],"id":"r118779","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-iExidLkKfTA\/XZWczOM8s4I\/AAAAAAAAee0\/2mzhSiN8oesk456HXlr7fSnDHzSNV7qZQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_6VwPJsKLSC0pcfmd.png","title":"Non-dairy Mexican chocolate ice cream","publishedAt":"2016-11-20T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"3.56 g","fat":"16.09 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"27.93 g","calories":"1122 kJ \/ 267 kcal"},"usefulItems":"shallow freezeable container, plastic wrap, freezer","hintsAndTricks":["Adjust the amount of ground chilli used in step 4 to your taste.","Use egg whites to make meringues.